## PLAN COLORS — import from lib/constants/planColors

Never hardcode plan color hex values in components.
Always use PLAN_COLORS[plan.color].border / .bg / .accent / .glow etc.

Available keys: mint, iris, coral, gold, purple, teal

Each key provides: label, border, bg, bgStrong, chip, chipBorder, chipText, accent, accentHover, gradient

Gradient values per key:
- mint:   linear-gradient(90deg, #1DBF8A, #34c99a)
- iris:   linear-gradient(90deg, #6385FF, #a78bfa)
- coral:  linear-gradient(90deg, #FF7B54, #FFD166)
- gold:   linear-gradient(90deg, #FFD166, #FFAA33)
- purple: linear-gradient(90deg, #a78bfa, #7C6AF7)
- teal:   linear-gradient(90deg, #34c99a, #0D5A46)

Set as CSS custom properties on the plan root element:
- --plan-accent
- --plan-accent-hover
- --plan-border
- --plan-bg
- --plan-bg-strong
- --plan-chip
- --plan-chip-border
- --plan-chip-text
- --plan-gradient

